===Etymology===
From late {{inh|en|enm|brik}}, {{m|enm|bryke}}, {{m|enm|bricke}}, from {{der|en|gml|-}} and {{der|en|dum|bricke}} {{gloss|"cracked or broken brick; tile-stone"; modern {{cog|nl|brik}}}}, ultimately related to {{der|en|gmw-pro|*brekan|t=to break}}, whence also {{cog|fro|briche}} and {{cog|fr|brique|t=brick}}. Compare also {{cog|nds-de|Brickje|t=small board, tray}}. Related to {{m|en|break}}.

